message.content:
Lithobates sphenocephalus is a species of frog commonly known as the southern leopard frog.
This frog can grow up to 4 inches in length and has a smooth, moist skin that is predominantly green or brown in color with scattered black spots.
Its skull has a distinctive wedge shape with a pointed snout.
The hind legs of the Lithobates sphenocephalus are long and muscular, allowing for powerful jumps and swimming.
This species is found in wetlands and slow-moving streams across the southeastern United States.
As an adaptable and opportunistic predator, the Lithobates sphenocephalus feeds on a variety of invertebrates, small vertebrates, and even other frogs.
Due to habitat loss and other threats, the conservation status of this species is of concern.
